<A>__{the hairdresser is pulling victoria's hair back into the widow's cape. for the first time, we see her face. it is set in a mask of severity.}
<C>__{ponsonby }
<D>__{... it will not surprise you to hear that she continues steadfast in her refusal to accept any public engagements, however trivial...}
<L>__{interior osborne house, queen victoria's bedchamber day}
<A>__{a bronze cast of prince albert's hand hangs above the royal bed. his sleeping gown is laid out on one side. a somberly dressed middle aged man stands by the bed: doctor jenner, the queen's physician. he is placing potions and medicaments in a row on the bedside table. behind him, two maidservants are busy stripping and remaking the bed while another raises the window to air the room.}
<C>__{ponsonby }
<D>__{... family and staff expend all their efforts endeavouring to draw her out of this state of unfettered morbidity, but to no avail. indeed, doctor jenner will not undertake to vouchsafe her sanity, unless some remedy is found...}
